---
description: Build and install Trident.app to /Applications
---

Build the Trident fork of Ghostty and install it to `/Applications/Trident.app`.

## Arguments

The user may pass `debug` as an argument to build a debug version. Otherwise, build a release version.

## Release Build (default)

1. Build libghostty with ReleaseFast optimization:
   ```
   zig build -Demit-macos-app=false -Doptimize=ReleaseFast
   ```

2. Build the macOS app with ReleaseLocal configuration:
   ```
   nix develop --command macos/build.nu --configuration ReleaseLocal
   ```

3. Install to /Applications:
   ```
   rm -rf /Applications/Trident.app && cp -R macos/build/ReleaseLocal/Trident.app /Applications/Trident.app
   ```

## Debug Build (when `debug` argument is passed)

1. Build libghostty without optimization:
   ```
   zig build -Demit-macos-app=false
   ```

2. Build the macOS app with Debug configuration:
   ```
   nix develop --command macos/build.nu --configuration Debug
   ```

3. Install to /Applications:
   ```
   rm -rf /Applications/Trident.app && cp -R macos/build/Debug/Trident.app /Applications/Trident.app
   ```

## Notes

- The zig build step must complete before the macOS app build
- ReleaseFast is required for release builds to avoid the "debug build" warning banner
- ReleaseLocal (not Release) is used because it includes the `disable-library-validation` entitlement needed for the ad-hoc-signed Sparkle framework
- Report success or failure after each step; do not continue if a step fails
